# Wedding Website Project Structure

This is a Next.js 15 wedding website project for Ale and Jesse. The main structure follows Next.js App Router conventions:

## Key Files
- **Entry Point**: [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - Main homepage component
- **Layout**: [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - Root layout with fonts and metadata
- **Styling**: [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) - Global CSS styles
- **Config**: [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration
- **TypeScript**: [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration with path aliases

## Path Aliases
- Use `@/*` to reference files from the `src/` directory (e.g., `@/components/Button`)

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 with App Router
- React 19
- TypeScript 5
- Tailwind CSS 4
- Lucide React for icons
- ESLint for code quality

## Development Commands
- `npm run dev` - Start development server with Turbopack
- `npm run build` - Build for production
- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint
